actions.text: Rule provides for consideration of the conference report to S. 5. During consideration of the conference report, points of order against the conference report for failure to comply with clause 3 of rule XXVIII are waived. The conference report shall be debatable for 90 minutes, proportionally divided and controlled.
The House Committee on Rules reported an original measure, H. Rept. 102-856, by Mr. Gordon.
Placed on the House Calendar, Calendar No. 195.
DEBATE - The House proceeded with one hour of debate.
The previous question was ordered without objection.
On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to by the Yeas and Nays: 329 - 71 (Roll No. 389).
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

official_title: Waiving points of order against the conference report to accompany the bill (S. 5) to grant employees family and temporary medical leave under certain circumstances, and for other purposes.

summary.text: Waives points of order against the consideration of the conference report to accompany S. 5 (family and temporary medical leave for employees).
